    {
      "question": "During an investigation of purchasing card (P-card) fraud at a manufacturing company, you discover that a warehouse supervisor has been making unauthorized personal purchases totaling $45,000 over 18 months. The supervisor used the company P-card to buy electronics, furniture, and appliances that were delivered to residential addresses. Which of the following controls would have been MOST effective in preventing this scheme?",
      "options": [
        "Requiring monthly reconciliation of P-card statements with supporting receipts and delivery addresses verified by an independent reviewer",
